i couldn_t breathe. there was just too much happening all at once. it seemed like voices were surrounding all of me. making it difficult to breathe. difficult to function. i couldn_t help the thousand thoughts running through my mind. making breathing harder by each second. it was like the world has come crashing down and i was the only one to witness it. everyone around me was the same but i was different. and hell  even the thought causes another one of these episodes. for there was always that small nagging thought at the back of my mind making it impossible to be at peace. i was smiling but i wasn_t happy. it was all a faade. it was a time-ticking bomb and slightest movement would make it burst. it was like a volcano waiting to erupt. i was nothing and everything all at once. i was afraid to do anything due to the fear that the bomb would go off. destroying me once again. leaving me as nothing. having to build myself back up every day. this was anxiety at its finest. submitted by @kamya.99  sumbit your story at bit.do/happystories or dm us. mentalhealth mentalhealthawareness stress anxiety depression selfcare help neverquit wellness peacefulmind selfhelp helpingothers bethechange trustyourself neverquit mentalstrength mentaltoughness helpingpeople anxious anxietyattack loveyourself believeinyourself embraceanxiety anxietyrelief beyou socialanxiety talkitout picture credits to the owner.

emotions  today i embrace every single emotion that runs through my entire multi dimensional being. ................. i spent the majority of my life (my old life before complete transformation) hiding and running from all of the feels because i didn_t know how to be with them. i was constantly frightened  riddled with anxiety and deep rooted depressions and allowing repeated experiences into my reality. this was my normal  i spent years emotional eating  taking drugs to self medicate and numb myself  drinking and basically on a constant road to self destruct. .............. today my normal is feeling all the feels with complete love  understanding  compassion  non-judgement and complete nurture for myself. i enjoy my being and my life that i have created while recognising my journey to get here and feeling complete gratitude. i love and value my life instead of constantly feeling like i wanted to end it. ................ constantly hearing as a child negative words  witnessing self destructive behaviours and hearing that life is hard and life isn_t fair leaves you growing up believing theses words and then maps out your entire life. ................ we need to be kind and nurture ourselves as adults  undo what has stood in our path to experiencing joy and allow our children to really bring forth the wisdom they are born with. give them a chance and you will see how amazing they are. .................... stop trying to control them just to appease your own inner turmoil and fear of being judged by others. not only do you suffer as a parent but your child does. .................... life is good  life is joyful  life is full of love. you just need to be able to see it. take the time to do the inner work and allow a new perspective to come through  i venting: i just wanna fucking forget you. i want to cut myself out of my skin in hope that this will finally stop fucking hurting. you don_t want nothin to do with me and it_s not like i did shit to you. and that_s what hurts so much. to know i gave you every bit of myself to know i gave and still give you everything. i was always loyal and did anything for you the best i could. it hurts to know that my best still wasn_t good enough and here i am. i have nothing  no one. you_re out having fun with your friends and whoever you_re rolling with now. i still love you so much  with every fucking ounce of my body  and you told me you don_t love me anymore and don_t want anything to do with me. i still think about what i could have done better. i gave you all my attention and time  i bought you gifts and love notes all the time. i always asked about your feelings and took care of you... i can_t do this anymore and i_m scared. i_m scared of others i_m scared to ask for help i_m scared of myself i_m overwhelmingly terrified of everything. i cry every night and sometimes in the day. my body hurts so much physically it_s thinking about you. and still... this is barley anything because i don_t want to write anything that_ll get me put on a list or put somewhere. i_m dying for you and if you knew you wouldn_t even care. you_ll never see this but that_s okay i guess. i_ll still never be able to talk bad about you because it_s not like you ever treated me that bad. i don_t know what happened. i guess you just fell out of it. i wish i could too. it_s been so long. this is the end.  depressed  depressionquotes  suicidaledits  depressionquotes  depression  suicidaledits  suicidal  suicidaltendencies  love  lovequotes  vent  venting  aesthetic

after reading news about the love island contestant sophie gradon taking her own life  it again highlights that depression or mental illness doesn_t look a particular way and that those who are truly suffering often hide it so well. it doesn_t matter how beautiful  rich  popular or happy people may appear on the surface and in particular on social media now a days it doesn_t mean they are not suffering inside and just because someone has the biggest smile doesn_t mean that it isn_t hiding a world of pain. looking at sophies profile only a few days ago she looked so happy and like she has it all  just goes to show how wrong that can be. those that need help often look like those don_t and so this is a shout out to all my beautiful friends  family  or people i know that you are not and never alone and that if you ever need anything i_m here  even if i don_t see you all the time don_t ever be afraid to reach out to me or others around you. if you ever need anything i will always be here  i will never judge you or think less of you  i love you all!!! anyone suffering with mental health out there just to let you know you are beautiful  you are loved and you are worth it! keep fighting! . . i wish the stigma surround mental health didn_t play such a role in preventing people from reaching out and getting the help they require! // g o o d . n e w s // do you need to hear some good news  there was a study about the effects of oula that was finished up earlier this year and it had awesome results!!! basically  it showed that oula can boost happiness  and lower depression and anxiety! how cool is that!! here is a little more information about the study:  from november 2016  january 2018  dr. tracy hellem and colleagues conducted a study that evaluated oula as an intervention for women with moderate levels of depression. women attended oula at least once per week for 12 weeks  and then abstained from oula for one week. depression  anxiety  and happiness were measured weekly. they found that over the course of the 12 weeks there was a trend in reduced depression and anxiety and increased happiness. when women abstained for oula after the 12 weeks  an increase in depression and anxiety was noted (see charts below). the researchers concluded that oula is a reasonable option to improve depression and anxiety  although further studies will be conducted to better understand the relationship between oula and depression and anxiety.  so remember  when you feel stressed  depressed  anxious  or just need a little happiness in your heart  hop into an oula class  hug a fellow oulakin if you need to  and leave feeling just a little lighter   oulafitness  modernmindbodyfitness  happyheart  mentalhealth  depression  anxiety  happiness  effectsofoula  feelgood  research  socool

grateful friday....where do i even start this week i just experienced a bucket list trip for so many people this past week. while i never really imagined myself going to alaska  i am beyond blessed that i was able to experience all the beauty there. alaska is pure  down to earth  jaw dropping gorgeous with such unique and beautiful wildlife. the best part of the trip though was spending time with my sister  katy. we laughed so hard and really just continued to strengthen and deepen our bond. she has supported and encouraged me for my entire life and is my number one cheerleader. the trip was physically and mentally challenging  and i know i was able to keep up and do all the things we did due to my training with dnrs. i am beyond grateful to have a toolbox to get me through any situation. i was able to eat all foods/drinks with no reactions. i was able to move more than i normally do with little pain. i was able to function on less sleep than i typically get at home  and experience no chronic fatigue. i still have work to do  and am beyond appreciative to have a network of individuals who are also going through the program who i can call on at any time or night for help and support.  now  i get to experience another adventure with my husband to an amazing resort in asheville  nc. i am fortunate to be able to live a laptop/smartphone lifestyle where i can work from anywhere.  nooffice. this to me is the true freedom in life. what are you grateful for this week i_d love you to share with me. i_ve learned that we can be grateful for the smallest things  and there is so much beauty in that.   dnrs  neuroplasticity  igotthis  limbicsystem  iamhappy  iamhealthy  iamstrong  iamenenergetic  dynamicneuralretrainingsystem  recoveringfromcfs  recoveryfromfibromyalgia  recoveryfromfoodsensitivies  recoveringfrominfectionsandviruses  recoveringfromchronicpain  recoveringfromanxiety

my days were spent clinging to my good friend depression  my nights weren_t any better. my disordered mind thought i was living life right   you_ll never make it  they would say  so stay with me . that_s exactly what i did. i slept and ate abnormally. my mind swimming with fears  and anxieties. the thought of school made me sick to my stomach  and mum thought i was faking. the nights were a fine line between death and life. every night i walked a tight rope  and every night i was afraid i would full. some nights i slept for hours  others i would stay up till 4am. looking up at the sky in wonder. wondering why i was placed on this earth if all i ever thought about was death or skinny. it wasn_t a life i was living. i wasn_t alive  but i was still living  and nothing hurt more than to scream  my lungs filling with water but nobody could hear me. my mind consumed with what could of been. i seem to be the family disappointment. my sister always said i was the pretty one  but i would take smart over pretty any day. my mum constantly asking what was wrong with me  made me think something was wrong with myself. my dad speaking  but i couldn_t hear a thing. tears flowing down my face  was i the only one who could see them why was i crying life was perfect. i should of been happy. why wasn_t i happy my mind. school. bed. school. bed. tear drops became my only friend. depression robbed me of my teenage years. suicidal thoughts took me from my friends. anxiety stole me from my family. words i couldn_t speak. i became mute. at sixteen i was just a lifeless body faking a smile. at eighteen i talked only when i had to. nineteen things started looking up  but only for a while. twenty  i took a breath of death. twenty one  life is good. i_m happy. i help people like me. i found veganism. i have created this platform of lovely souls. my days are consumed with hand holds  and cuddles from the patients i work with. the sun is out in my mind. i find joy in collecting flowers.reading books. and hearing others life stories.i cuddle my dog more. i laugh more. i say  i love you more . and if there was anything i would tell my teenage self  it truly does get better.i promise.
